### Inheritance in C#

Inheritance allows a class to inherit members (fields, properties, methods) from another class. It promotes code reuse and establishes a hierarchical relationship.

### Base and Derived Classes

```csharp
// Base class
public class Animal
{
    public string Name { get; set; }

    public void Eat()
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"{Name} is eating");
    }
}

// Derived class
public class Dog : Animal
{
    public void Bark()
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"{Name} is barking");
    }
}
```

### Using Inherited Members

```csharp
Dog dog = new Dog();
dog.Name = "Buddy";      // From Animal
dog.Eat();                // From Animal
dog.Bark();               // From Dog
```

### The base Keyword

Access base class members from derived class:

```csharp
public class Dog : Animal
{
    public Dog(string name) : base(name) { }  // Call base constructor

    public void Display()
    {
        base.Eat();  // Explicitly call base method
    }
}
```

### Constructor Inheritance

```csharp
public class Vehicle
{
    public string Brand { get; }

    public Vehicle(string brand)
    {
        Brand = brand;
    }
}

public class Car : Vehicle
{
    public string Model { get; }

    public Car(string brand, string model) : base(brand)
    {
        Model = model;
    }
}
```

### Sealed Classes

Prevent further inheritance:

```csharp
public sealed class FinalClass { }
// public class Derived : FinalClass { }  // Error
```

### Inheritance Chain

```csharp
public class LivingThing { }
public class Animal : LivingThing { }
public class Mammal : Animal { }
public class Dog : Mammal { }
```

### Inheritance Rules

| Rule | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Single inheritance | A class can inherit from only one base class |
| Multi-level | A -> B -> C is allowed |
| Multiple interfaces | A class can implement multiple interfaces |
| Object base | All types implicitly inherit from `System.Object` |

> **Key Point:** C# supports single inheritance (one base class). Use `:` to specify inheritance. The derived class calls the base constructor using `: base()`. Private members are not inherited. Use `sealed` to prevent inheritance.

### Object Class Members

All classes inherit these from `System.Object`:

```csharp
Equals()      // Compare objects
GetHashCode() // Hash code for dictionaries
ToString()    // String representation
GetType()     // Runtime type
```

codeExample:
using System;

public class Employee
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public decimal Salary { get; set; }

    public Employee(string name, decimal salary)
    {
        Name = name;
        Salary = salary;
    }

    public void Work() => Console.WriteLine($"{Name} is working");
}

public class Manager : Employee
{
    public int TeamSize { get; set; }

    public Manager(string name, decimal salary, int teamSize)
        : base(name, salary)
    {
        TeamSize = teamSize;
    }

    public void Manage() => Console.WriteLine($"{Name} manages {TeamSize} people");
}

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        var mgr = new Manager("Alice", 80000, 5);
        mgr.Work();
        mgr.Manage();
    }
}
